<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-07-28T02:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-07-28T02:00:00-05:00" n="528" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d528">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.001 Chiang Kai-shek/7–2849:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Taipei</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Macdonald</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Taipei</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-07-28T16:00:00+09:00">July 28,
                                    1949—4 p. m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received July 28—1:02 p. m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>325. Reliably informed that Generalissimo will remain Taiwan only 1 week
                            [to] complete organization new offices here, then proceed Chungking and
                            Lanchow. Quirino [and] he may go Korea for Far East Union Conference
                            middle August. New signatories to pact may subscribe only to principles
                            or to one or more material commitments depending on each nation’s
                            desire.</p>
                        <p>Repeated Canton 137.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Macdonald</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>